<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> out of one’s sight • out of sight</xh5><p> <i>out of one’s sight—</i>no longer visible; unseen: He was already <u>out of my sight</u>, but only a couple hundred feet ahead.</p><p><i>out of sight—</i>1. <i>= out of one’s sight: </i>They still stood there upon the rocks, waving till the ship was <u>out of sight</u>. 2. <i>(coll., of prices)</i> exorbitant: People found that home prices were <u>out of sight</u> even before they entered the housing market. 3. <i>(sl.)</i> used as a generalized expression of admiration: For an official person he’s absolutely <u>out of sight</u>.</p> </entry>
